      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RIGHTEOUS FURY (1) turned in a better run last time to find a minor placing (22.39) at Ballarat behind Zipping Sandchez in a Grade 5. Got back and turned spotting a start but found the line impressively. Must come into calculations. PAW PRYDI (3) flew the lids with a fast early split and led until late but gathered in when a half a length second at Bendigo over 425m in 24.11. Can measure up. KRAKEN BABE (2) is a well performed dog who recorded her 7th career win last time out at Bendigo (24.11). Has a good record here at this journey. Leading chance again. GRAFFITI (7) was unplaced here last start but gets his chance to atone.",
